  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Blanch 2 bell peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes, then rinse with cold water to stop the cooking process.",
    "In a blender or food processor, combine blanched bell peppers, onion, garlic, allspice, thyme, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper. Blend until smooth.",
    "Transfer the pepper mixture to individual mini cocottes and top with a sprinkle of cornstarch to create a crust.",
    "Drizzle 1 tablespoon of coconut oil over each cocotte and cover with foil.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, then remove foil and continue baking for an additional 10 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve hot."
  ],
